- Hire you?

14:17.648 --> 14:20.985
- Steve, are you sure about this?
- Stop treating me like a kid.

14:21.152 --> 14:24.030
I was right about the pole, wasn't I?

14:28.868 --> 14:31.913
It's working.

14:32.080 --> 14:36.751
Soon the beam of light will show us
the exact location of the...

14:36.918 --> 14:40.505
Steve, what have you done?
You've ruined everything.

14:40.671 --> 14:42.548
I'm sorry, Dad. I'm...

14:42.715 --> 14:45.468
A genius. Look.

14:46.469 --> 14:50.014
"Lastly, tip your hat
in the Garden of Eden."

14:50.181 --> 14:53.184
- It's the last clue.
- Really?

14:53.351 --> 14:57.437
- Sorry, it's been a really long night.
- The Garden of Eden.

14:57.604 --> 14:59.397
I'm on it.

14:59.564 --> 15:02.901
I'm gonna need two tickets on
your next flight to the Garden of Eden.

15:03.068 --> 15:06.279
The Garden of Eden. The first garden.

15:06.446 --> 15:08.365
You don't fly to biblical allegories?

15:08.532 --> 15:11.201
See, this is why you people
are going out of business.

15:11.368 --> 15:14.663
I've got it. The first national garden.

15:17.999 --> 15:20.585
But this is the only peanut plant
in this whole place.

15:20.752 --> 15:22.254
The hat has gotta be in here.

15:22.420 --> 15:24.714
- It's empty.
- It's a dead end.

15:24.881 --> 15:26.466
Fudge.

15:26.633 --> 15:29.135
Wait, Steve.
Don't declare fudge just yet.

15:29.302 --> 15:31.096
Look, the symbol.

15:31.263 --> 15:35.016
And the pot is shaped like a hat.
It's the last piece of the puzzle.

15:35.183 --> 15:39.271
Wait a minute. Monocle, cane, hat...

15:39.437 --> 15:42.524
All the clues
are things that President Peanut wears.

15:42.691 --> 15:44.818
Great work, Steve. All we need now...

15:44.985 --> 15:47.863
...is a 20-foot peanut
with presidential aspirations.

15:48.029 --> 15:50.657
- To the lowa caucuses.
- No, Dad.

15:50.824 --> 15:53.660
What we need is a 20-foot president.

15:59.165 --> 16:02.878
Of course.
Lincoln was the father of the conspiracy.

16:03.044 --> 16:06.798
The original President Peanut.
Well, here goes.

16:21.061 --> 16:23.147
Oh, God.

16:23.314 --> 16:28.027
- The jar of proof must be in there.
- Hidden up Lincoln's proof chute.

16:28.193 --> 16:30.904
We did it, Dad. Soon the whole world
will know the truth.

16:31.071 --> 16:33.866
Nothing can stop us now.

16:44.043 --> 16:46.045
I'll go first.

16:47.546 --> 16:51.717
Careful. These stairs
will be dangerous without a banister.

16:51.884 --> 16:53.594
Dad.

16:53.761 --> 16:57.556
Dad. Dad. Dad.

16:57.723 --> 16:59.933
Dad. Dad.

17:00.100 --> 17:03.979
Almost there, Dad.
Hey, look. Funny pages from 1916.

17:04.146 --> 17:06.190
The Katzenjammer Kids.

17:06.357 --> 17:08.817
Let's see.
They're putting their dad in a barrel...

17:08.983 --> 17:10.944
...and rolling it down a steep hill.

17:11.111 --> 17:13.405
And now he's injured.

17:14.531 --> 17:17.826
That's not funny.
I guess comedy's really evolved.

17:17.992 --> 17:20.496
Thanks, Harvard.

17:20.662 --> 17:22.830
And that's where babies come from.

17:22.998 --> 17:26.001
Look out, Dad.

17:26.167 --> 17:28.796
I can't believe there's lava
under Washington, D.C.

17:28.962 --> 17:32.841
Where do you think
all the hot air comes from?

17:41.766 --> 17:45.436
- Oh, my God, I see it. I'm going in.
- Finally.

17:52.944 --> 17:55.029
Okay, your turn.

17:57.532 --> 17:59.158
Come on, already.

18:01.410 --> 18:03.496
Hot air.

18:03.663 --> 18:05.873
Politics.

18:06.040 --> 18:07.208
Funny.

18:07.375 --> 18:09.961
Dad, there it is.

18:11.629 --> 18:13.548
The jar of proof.

18:18.344 --> 18:21.430
Can't reach it. Steve, I'll help you up.

18:26.185 --> 18:29.814
- Booby trap.
- There's something inside.

18:29.981 --> 18:32.942
It's a playbill from the night
Lincoln was assassinated.

18:33.109 --> 18:36.529
It's got his blood and all the names
he considered for peanut butter.

18:36.696 --> 18:38.573
Yeah, yeah. Now hand it over.

18:38.739 --> 18:41.492
Now the world
can know the truth, right, Dad?

18:41.659 --> 18:43.870
Yeah, sure. Give me, give me.

18:45.955 --> 18:47.373
Finally, the...

18:47.540 --> 18:52.378
Wait. This isn't the jar of proof.
He switched them on me.

18:52.545 --> 18:53.796
Steve.

18:53.963 --> 18:55.006
You're one of them.

18:55.172 --> 18:58.801
You don't care about the truth.
You're just gonna destroy it.

18:58.968 --> 19:02.846
- It's over, boy. Give me the jar.
- President Jimmy Carter?

19:03.013 --> 19:06.224
That's right.
The second President Peanut.

19:07.058 --> 19:08.643
I'm sorry, son.

19:08.810 --> 19:11.271
When were you gonna tell me
you were Illuminutti?

19:11.438 --> 19:13.857
Steve, that's crazy.
I was never gonna tell you.

19:14.024 --> 19:16.860
All this time, I thought
I was proving I was so grown-up...

19:17.027 --> 19:19.404
...but you saw me as a stupid kid
you could use...

19:19.571 --> 19:21.406
...to find your precious jar of proof.

19:21.573 --> 19:24.075
Precious indeed. Without this secret...

19:24.242 --> 19:26.494
...our young nation
would have never survived.

19:26.661 --> 19:30.332
Steve, if you were a grownup, you'd
understand why we have to destroy it.

19:30.498 --> 19:33.835
- The truth would tear this country apart.
- Maybe back then.

19:34.002 --> 19:36.713
But America's a big boy now,
and so am I.

19:36.880 --> 19:38.298
We can handle the truth...

19:38.465 --> 19:41.217
...whether it's about bedtime
or black people.

19:43.219 --> 19:45.722
Enough. Give me the jar
and let's be done with it.

19:45.889 --> 19:48.975
- Dad, don't do it.
- Trust me, son.

19:49.142 --> 19:52.395
I'm doing the grown-up thing here.

19:55.482 --> 19:59.277
And so the safety of our nation
will forever be ensured.

19:59.444 --> 20:02.280
God bless Ameri...

20:09.996 --> 20:11.373
Let's get out of here.

20:19.047 --> 20:22.467
Wow, Dad, you switched jars on him.
That was so awesome.

20:22.634 --> 20:26.220
Well, I learned it from you.
I guess maybe you are all grown-up.

20:26.387 --> 20:27.429
Thanks, Dad.

20:27.596 --> 20:30.432
Now come on.
We've got some truth to spread.

20:30.599 --> 20:32.726
Wait. That's the wrong jar.

20:32.893 --> 20:36.230
- What? That's impossible.
- You made the switch. What happened?

20:36.397 --> 20:40.442
I had to make the switch? I thought
it was a magic backpack or something.

20:40.609 --> 20:42.444
No, it wasn't.

20:42.611 --> 20:44.571
Now the world
will never know the truth.

20:44.738 --> 20:49.201
If only there was a place you could make
any claim you want with no proof...

20:49.368 --> 20:51.954
...and millions of people would
accept it as fact.

20:52.121 --> 20:53.163
That's it.

20:54.540 --> 20:56.625
Thanks for taking that block off, Dad.

20:56.792 --> 20:58.293
Well, you're a young man now.

20:58.460 --> 21:01.046
You're ready for everything
the Internet has to offer.

21:01.213 --> 21:04.091
- Even porn.
- Wow, porn.

21:04.258 --> 21:07.302
This is the best Black History Month
ever.

21:51.262 --> 21:53.347
[ENGLISH]
